    <h4>Brooke Balick</h4>
    <h5>Head of Development / Executive Producer</h5>
    <p>A seasoned development, casting and production executive, Brooke has been in television for more than fifteen years, working on everything from blue chip docs and man reality shows to ludicrous house elimination formats and poplicious soap docs. She has experience as a network and third party development executive and has created and shaped hundreds of hours of programming for networks including VH1, MTV, Bravo, TLC, A&E, Sundance, HGTV, Food Network, Travel, Discovery, NatGeo, History and Science.</p>
    <p>Whether she's embedded with rappers, hermits, sexperts, seniors or adventurers, her curiosity always grants her access into unique worlds and big characters that make for dynamic TV.</p>
    <br>
    <h4>Peter Van Pelt</h4>
    <h5>Executive Producer / Showrunner</h5>
    <p>Peter accidentally started working in reality TV when he interned on a little show called America's Funniest Home Videos.  He's a creative executive who knows how to create storylines and shape content and since that first job, he's punched up scripts for B-movie king Roger Corman, delved into every food origin imaginable, investigated historical and medical mysteries (History Detectives, Dr. G), run more than 200 episodes of History's biggest hit to date (Pawn Stars), overseen psychic matchmaking, helped kids talk to parents about sex (Dr. Drew’s Sex with Mom & Dad) and shaped stories for the toughest (Yukon) men on earth.</p>
